        <div class="info-callout">
          <p><strong>These brackets apply to taxable income, not gross income.</strong> Taxable income is your gross income minus your deduction (standard or itemized). A single filer with $85,000 gross income and the $15,000 standard deduction has $70,000 of taxable income, which puts them in the 22% bracket for the top portion only.</p>
        </div>
